The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, March 22 : MSV Al Rafiqyuei, a dhow sailing from Dubai to Mogadishu in Somalia, with a crew of 16 Indians and a cargo containing rice, refined oil and wheat was hijacked this morning east of Somalian coast, directorate of shipping officials said.           
	Officials said the Indian navy vessel and the forces of other countries operating in the Gulf of Aden have been informed and asked to provide immediate assistance.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): Prosecution has sought postponement of the 26/11 Mumbai terror attack trial from March 23 to April 13 citing inadequate security arrangements at the makeshift court in the Arthur Road jail complex. Ajmal Kasab, the lone terrorist caught alive in the attack, is among the accused who will face trial.                  
	 London (PTI): Three British teenagers who pleaded guilty to the killing of an Indian sailor in Southampton in October 2007 have been sentenced to six and a half years in jail. Gregory Fernandes, 32, was the victim of a racist attack by the teenagers who had boasted that they wanted to beat a Paki.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Election Commission on Saturday discussed the controversial speeches of Varun Gandhi but no decision was taken. The commission discussed the replies filed by Varun and the BJP, officials said.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): A Mumbai court on Saturday remanded the 60-year-old businessman, who had allegedly raped his two daughters, to police custody till March 26. The businessmans wife and the tantrik, Hasmukh Rathod, at whose behest the crime was supposedly committed, have also been remanded to police custody.                  
	 Kochi (PTI): A cardinal in Kerala has claimed nuns are being discriminated against and treated shoddily by priests who force them to wash clothes and cook. The admissions were made by Mar Varkey Vithayathil in a book written by him.                                                                                                                           
